# CRATS Protocol Production Indexer (`crats-indexer`) — Full 4-Layer Implementation Plan

This implementation plan outlines the architecture, database schema, event projections, and API engines for the **CRATS Protocol Indexer (`crats-indexer`)**.

The indexer captures **every inch of data**, price attestations, vault yield calculations, fee accruals, DMS hashes, carbon credit batch vints, compliance restrictions, and secondary P2P beneficial ownership register (BOR v2) updates across all 4 layers of the CRATS EVM Protocol.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Infrastructure**: The indexer uses Prisma ORM connected to MySQL / PostgreSQL. All blockchain events are ingested in strict block-sequential order with automatic chain re-org handling (rolling back projections on parent hash mismatch).

> [!TIP]
> **Real-Time WebSockets & GraphQL API**: The indexer exposes both a REST/GraphQL query layer and WebSocket subscriptions for instant updates to CopyM applications (Admin Web, Investor Web, Issuer Web).

